===Etymology===
[[File:Lucas Cranach d.Ä. (Werkst.) - Porträt des Martin Luther (Lutherhaus Wittenberg).jpg|thumb|''Portrait of Martin Luther'' (1528) by the workshop of {{w|Lucas Cranach the Elder}}, from the collection of the {{w|Lutherhaus}} in [[Wittenberg]], [[Saxony-Anhalt]], [[Germany]]]]

From the [[surname]] of German [[theologian]] and [[ecclesiastical]] [[reformer]] {{w|Martin Luther}} (1483–1546) {{suffix|en||an}}.

{{m|en|Luther}} is from an {{etyl|goh|en}} given name, from {{m|goh|liut||people}} + {{m|goh|heri||army}} (from {{der|en|gem-pro|*harjaz||army; commander, warrior}}, from {{der|der|ine-pro|*kóryos||war; troops}}, from {{m|ine-pro|*ker-||army}}).

